). Aquilolamnids and giant pachycormids all became extinct at the Cretaceous–Paleogene (K–Pg) event and were ecologically replacedduring the early Paleogene (Paleocene) by pelagic planktivorous batoids (

Archaeomanta

, 

Sulcidens

